## Coding in valid data and recoding values

<code>
#recode 7 values as 1 in this example
data1['H1GI11']=data1['H1GI11'].replace(7, 1)

print 'H1GI11 with 7 recoded as set to 1'
I11b = data1['H1GI11'].value_counts(sort=True, dropna=False)
print(I11b)

<output> 
H1GI11 with 7 recoded as set to 1
1.000000    6100
0.000000     399
nan            5
Name: H1GI11, dtype: int64

